Given the application is open
And the user has at least one item in the shopping cart
When the user navigates to the shopping cart page
And the user clicks the "Remove" or "X" icon next to an item
Then the selected item should be successfully removed from the shopping cart
And the cart summary should be updated
And the total price should be recalculated

Gherkin

Feature: Remove Product from Shopping Cart

  As a user of the Style Haven e-commerce platform,
  I want to be able to remove items from my shopping cart,
  So that I can finalize my order with the correct items.

  Scenario: Successfully remove an item from the shopping cart
    Given the application is open
    And the user has at least one item in the shopping cart
    When the user navigates to the "Shopping Cart" page
    And the user clicks the "Remove" button for a specific item
    Then the selected item should be removed from the cart
    And the shopping cart subtotal and total price should be updated accordingly
    And a confirmation message "Item removed successfully" should be displayed